This project is a derivative work based on the following third-party
software and assets:


1. CannonSmash (original game)
   Copyright (C) 2002-2006  Cannon Smith (cannon.smith@cannonsmash.com)
   Source: https://cannonsmash.sourceforge.net/
   License: GNU General Public License v2.0

   CannonSmash Web is a browser-based remake and derivative of the
   original CannonSmash. The physics engine (ball flight, bounce,
   shot solver, ball state machine) is a direct port of the original
   C++ code. Game rules, AI behaviour, player archetype concepts,
   and control feel are derived from the original work.

   In July 2026, the original React/three.js prototype was discarded
   and the project was fully redesigned and reimplemented by Claude
   (Anthropic's "Fable" model) based on the faithful physics port,
   reverse-engineering notes, the original's known feel, and the
   designer's specification. The resulting codebase is a complete
   from-scratch rewrite using vanilla TypeScript + three.js.


